    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-07-26</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-22T21:48:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Truth in Video Game Rating Act - Requires the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) to prescribe rules to prohibit as an unfair and deceptive act or practice: (1) providing a content rating of any video or computer game labeled for sale or distribution in interstate commerce without having reviewed the game's content in its entirety; (2) withholding, hiding, or failing to disclose any content of such a game to the person assigning such rating; or (3) providing a rating that grossly mischaracterizes a game's content.</p> <p>Requires the Comptroller General to study and report to Congress on game content ratings systems and related questions.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
